sols_latex:
A quick application of the chain rule gives

\begin{align*}
\frac{d}{dx}(\sin^{-1}(\sqrt{x})) &= \frac{1}{\sqrt{1-(\sqrt{x})^{2}}}\frac{d}{dx}(\sqrt{x})\\
&= \frac{1}{\sqrt{1-x}}\frac{1}{2\sqrt{x}}\\
&= \frac{1}{2\sqrt{x-x^{2}}}
\end{align*}

